<TITLE> BNP plans 10-day programme on Zia's death anniversary </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 15 (bdnews24.com)  BNP has decided to observe a 10-day programme to commemorate the 39th death anniversary of its founder Ziaur Rahman. The decision was made at meeting presided over by Secretary general Khandaker Delwar Hossain at the Party's Naya Paltan office on Saturday. The programme will kick off with a central convention of the party in Dhaka on May 29. Other events include hoisting of party flags at half mast and black and national flags at their offices around the country, wearing black badges, placing wreaths at Zia's grave at Sher-e-Bangla Nagar, Milad Mahfils and blood donation drive. Following her visit to Ziaur Rahman's grave on May 30, opposition leader Khaleda Zia will distribute food among the poor. The party and its associate organisations will be putting up posters and handing out leaflets on the occasion. Associate organisations will be organising several meetings to be held in between May 31 and June 7. BNP's cultural wing, JASAS, will also host a photography exhibition at the national press club. Former president Ziaur Rahman was assassinated by a group of renegade army officers at Chittagong circuit house on May 30, 1981. Vice-president Altaf Hossain Chowdhury, chairperson's advisor Shamsuzzaman Dudu, and other senior leaders were present at the meeting. b
